A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Neighborhood Cooperative Ministries; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, for over thirty-six years, Neighborhood Cooperative Ministries (NCM) has been
3 serving southwestern Gwinnett County by providing food, clothing, short term financial
4 assistance, and job placement services to families in need; and
5 WHEREAS, NCM was formed as a collaboration of serval churches, individuals, and social
6 and civic organizations to help serve neighbors in crisis, transforming lives through the love
7 of Christ; and
8 WHEREAS, NCM has continued to grow as the needs in the area increase, adding new
9 ministries focusing on personal empowerment, including a job ministry, financial
10 management classes, children's programs, case management, and spiritual programs; and
11 WHEREAS, in the past five years, NCM has responded to the COVID-19 crisis, overhauled
12 its technology and website, hired its first part-time controller, partnered with numerous new
13 organizations, and completed serval renovation, construction, and expansion projects; and
